'''Jordy Josué Caicedo Medina''' (born 18 November 1997) is an Ecuadorian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Striker (association football)|striker]] for Argentine club [[Club Atlético Huracán|Huracán]], on loan from Mexican club [[Atlas F.C.|Atlas]], and the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]].

==Club career==
Caicedo started playing football recreationally from an early age; he has stated that he would play football "in rich boy neighborhoods, bet money and always won."<ref name="br">{{Cite web |title=Primeiro equatoriano do Vitória, Jordy Caicedo revela intimidade |url=https://www.correio24horas.com.br/ec-vitoria/primeiro-equatoriano-do-vitoria-jordy-caicedo-revela-intimidade-0819 |access-date=2025-11-21 |website=www.correio24horas.com.br |language=pt-br}}</ref> At the age of 15, he had an unsuccessful trial with [[Santos FC]] in Brazil.<ref name="br"/> He has been compared to Ecuador international [[Felipe Caicedo]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Vásconez |first=Lucía |last2=Bayas |first2=Mauricio |date=2017-01-21 |title=Jordy Josué Caicedo, goleador que delira con el encocado |url=https://www.elcomercio.com/deportes/jordyjosuecaicedo-goleador-ecuador-encocado-sub20/ |access-date=2025-11-21 |website=El Comercio |language=es}}</ref> In February 2021, he joined Bulgarian club [[PFC CSKA Sofia|CSKA Sofia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cska.bg/index.php?main_page=document_general_info&products_id=9669 |title=Официално: ЦСКА привлече Жорди Кайседо |publisher=cska.bg |language=Bulgarian |date=5 February 2021|accessdate=16 July 2022}}</ref> In July 2022, Caicedo relocated to Mexico, signing a contract with [[Tigres UANL]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eluniverso.com/deportes/ecuatorianos-exterior/jordy-caicedo-firma-millonario-acuerdo-con-tigres-de-monterrey-hasta-el-2026-y-se-declara-listo-para-hacer-dupla-con-cualquiera-nota/ |title=Jordy Caicedo firma millonario acuerdo con Tigres de Monterrey hasta el 2026 y se declara 'listo para hacer dupla con cualquiera'|publisher=eluniverso.com |language=Spanish |date=5 July 2022|accessdate=16 July 2022}}</ref>

On 15 July 2024, Caicedo was loaned from [[Atlas F.C.|Atlas]] to Spanish [[Segunda División]] side [[Sporting de Gijón]], for one year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realsporting.com/noticias/el-sporting-incorpora-a-jordy-caicedo|title=El Sporting incorpora a Jordy Caicedo|trans-title=Sporting sign Jordy Caicedo|publisher=Sporting Gijón|language=es|date=15 July 2024|accessdate=16 July 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Caicedo made his [[Ecuador national football team|senior national team]] debut on 4 June 2021 in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|World Cup qualifying]] match against Brazil. He substituted [[Enner Valencia]] in the 76th minute.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[ESPN]]|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/lineups?gameId=561066|title=Brazil v Ecuador game report|date=4 June 2021}}</ref>

Caicedo made his debut in a professional tournament later that month in the [[2021 Copa América]], coming on as a second half substitute in the opening match against [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=13 June 2021|title=Colombia se impuso 1-0 a Ecuador en la Copa América|url=https://www.elcomercio.com/deportes/copa-america/colombia-ecuador-debut-copa-america-brasil-futbol.html|access-date=18 June 2021|website=El Comercio|language=es-EC}}</ref> Caicedo scored his first goal for the senior national team on 25 March 2022, converting a penalty in another World Cup qualifying match against [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]] in a 3-1 loss.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.si.com/soccer/2022/03/25/ecuador-uruguay-qualify-2022-world-cup-south-america|title=Ecuador, Uruguay Claim South America's Remaining Automatic World Cup Berths|date=24 March 2022|access-date=26 March 2022}}</ref>

